\begin_layout Subsubsection
Vice Ridden (2 vices)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
All Seventh Sons start with the Vice-Ridden merit: They start with two Vices,
 but may only regain a willpower from either once per session.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Know Vice
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
A seventh son can immediately recognize the vice of anyone they can see.
 If the character does not have a vice, the Seventh Son is aware of that
 fact instead.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Knowledge of the Vice
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Seventh Son gets a +2 to any dice rolls to for interactions with a character
 that shares a vice with them.
 This includes both social, and combat rolls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
How similar a vice much be is flexible and is up to GM discretion, for example
 the vice of Slothful and Lazyness are normally close enough.
\end_layout

